//NOTE TO TRANSLATORS: KEEP THE FORMATTING - it's for the correct colors
 
@4850 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-<CHARNAME>! The world feels wide again — the air, the light, even the sound of your footsteps!~
@4851 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-If we could bottle freedom, it would sound just like that — and sparkle twice as bright!~
@4852 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-No more bottles, Tippledew — ever. I’d rather sleep in a dragon’s mouth than in another jar!~
@4853 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Have you come to make a wish, or to solve some riddles?~
@4854 = ~A wish, perhaps… can you really grant one?~
@4855 = ~You want to ask riddles? Go ahead.~
@4856 = ~Stop sparkling near my face, please.~
@4857 = ~Just passing through, little ones.~
@4858 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-We’re free!~
@4859 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-The hero <CHARNAME> has freed us!~
@4860 = ~Oh, it’s so wonderful to see you both again!~
@4861 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Brother Edrim! You won’t be angry if we start tugging at your robe again, will you?~
@4862 = ~No, certainly not. You may tease me as much as you like — I’m just glad you’re safe.~
@4863 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-I tell you, that was *quite* an adventure!~
@4864 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-And all that adventuring makes one terribly sleepy!~
@4865 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Yes, Lilafern. Let’s rest — but not before we thank our rescuer properly.~
@4866 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-A hundred blessings and a hundred sparkles upon you, <CHARNAME>! We’d have kissed your feet if they weren’t so terribly smelly.~
@4867 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Thank you, <CHARNAME> — truly. You’ve given us back the light, the laughter, and the lovely little chaos we missed. We’ll never forget how you made the world noisy again.~
@4868 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Wait! We can’t just let <PRO_HIMHER> go without a wish! That would be... ungrateful, or possibly unlucky — or both!~
@4869 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Exactly right, Lilafern! A small gift, a little sparkle to keep the dark away. What will you have, <CHARNAME>?~
@4870 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-So! One wish, <CHARNAME>. Only one — we’re not genies, you know? You can pick your sparkle: Resistance to poisons, shields against spells, a shimmer of luck against hostile wands, a charm against awkward transformations, or maybe... a little fortitude against very bad dragon breath? Choose wisely, <CHARNAME> — even tiny wishes have echoes.~
@4871 = ~I’d rather be safe from poison and disease.~
@4872 = ~Perhaps something to resist spells.~
@4873 = ~A little resistance to wands and magical devices wouldn’t hurt.~
@4874 = ~I could use a safeguard against being turned into something unnatural.~
@4875 = ~Maybe something to help me get through danger — like dragon’s breath.~
@4876 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-A wise choice! Hold still — this won’t sparkle much... or maybe it will.~
@4877 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-There! A touch of moonlight, a pinch of laughter, and a dusting of please-don’t-die.~
@4878 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Look, Tippledew! A clumsy hooman!~
@4879 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Oh hush, Lilafern! It's an adventurer, silly! You can always tell by <PRO_HISHER> fierce look.~
@4880 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Welcome to Duskwood Dell, tall one!~
@4881 = ~Who are you?~
@4882 = ~Who's speaking there?~
@4883 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-The tall one returns — and still unsparkly, I see!~
@4884 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-We are the Dell-Light Twins, keepers of night giggles and guardians of… well, nothing terribly important.~
@4885 = ~Dell-Light Twins?~
@4886 = ~Yes, but what are you? Two glowing dots?~
@4887 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-A fitting name, don’t you think? We’re making Duskwood Dell lightful!~
@4888 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-For those who delight the Dell not only in daylight, of course.~
@4889 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-We’re faeries, silly! Too small for your eyes, too quick for your hands.~
@4890 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Duskwood Dell is our home! Someone has to keep this peace-loving crowd from dozing off.~
@4891 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Lilafern: ^-It’s called Duskwood Dell, after all — not Deskwood Dull!~
@4892 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Anyway. Have you come to make a wish, or to solve some riddles?~
@4893 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-A riddle! A game! Let’s test the tall one’s brain!~
@4894 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Oh yes! Riddles are like sparkles – they reveal who’s dull!~
@4895 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Already forgotten? You’ve won, remember. No more riddles for now.~
@4896 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-At least, not for a while.~
@4897 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Listen then, wanderer of the Dell:
	"I am not alive, yet I grow.  
	I have no lungs, yet I need air.  
	I have no mouth, yet water kills me.  
	What am I?"~
@4898 = ~Shurely a mushroom.~
@4899 = ~You’re talking about fire.~
@4900 = ~A shadow, perhaps?~
@4901 = ~A gelatinous cube.~
@4902 = ~That’s a silly question. None of those things exist.~
@4903 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Fire?! ...Fire, <PRO_HESHE> said fire!~
@4904 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-That’s cheating!~
@4905 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-We spent an hour polishing that riddle!~
@4906 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Next time we’ll ask about metamagics or psionics!~
@4907 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Fine! You win... but only because you’re taller.~
@4908 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Oh, lovely guess! Entirely wrong, but lovely!~
@4909 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^- We adore confidence more than accuracy!~
@4910 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Try before we start giving *hints* that make it worse.~
@4911 = ~All right, I’ll try again.~
@4912 = ~No more riddles for now.~
@4913 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Oh, a skeptic! How *refreshing!*~
@4914 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Let’s tickle <PRO_HIMHER> anyway, just for balance!~
@4915 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-No, no, <PRO_HESHE>’s funny. We’ll keep <PRO_HIMHER> for riddles later.~
@4916 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Oh! No more riddles? How tragic!~
@4917 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Come, Tippledew — let’s find someone who appreciates confusion!~
@4918 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-All right then, another riddle! Listen closely:
"I lurk in dungeons patiently.
I feast on those who walk too greedily.
Be bold, come close,
and see what lingers —
I glitter for gold,
and charge in fingers.  
What am I?"~
@4919 = ~A ghost, perhaps?~
@4920 = ~A doppleganger.~
@4921 = ~An echo.~
@4922 = ~A mimic.~
@4923 = ~That’s nonsense. You just made that up.~
@4924 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-No, <PRO_HESHE> knew; <PRO_HESHE> actually knew!~
@4925 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-That was supposed to be unsolvable!~
@4926 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Did you bribe a mindflayer for answers?~
@4927 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Fine, clever <PRO_RACE>. You win again. But next time, we’ll make it rhyme in Draconic!~
@4928 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-We adore confidence more than accuracy!~
@4929 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Try again before we start giving *terrible* hints.~
@4930 = ~I’ve had enough of your riddles.~
@4931 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Mocking the questioner? Bold move!~
@4932 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Let’s tickle <PRO_HIMHER> anyway, just for fun!~
@4933 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-We’ll see if <PRO_HESHE> laughs in echo.~
@4934 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Another challenge! The riddle of mud and majesty!~
@4935 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Listen well, wanderer:  
"I live in the quiet, I sing in the rain.  
I leap without fear, yet I never complain.  
My crown is of mud, my throne a bog.  
Kiss me, and you’ll turn into a...?"~
@4936 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Choose wisely! The wrong kiss can last forever!~
@4937 = ~A dog.~
@4938 = ~A hog.~
@4939 = ~A frog.~
@4940 = ~A vampire.~
@4941 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Frog, <PRO_HESHE> actually said frog!~
@4942 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Unbelievable!~
@4943 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Fine, clever <PRO_RACE>, you win. Again. Stop being right, it’s annoying.~
@4944 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Next time we’ll ask something unsolvable. Like the mating habits of flumphs.~
@4945 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Oh, wonderful! Entirely wrong, but so confident!~
@4946 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-We cherish enthusiasm almost as much as accuracy!~
@4947 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Try again before we start kissing random guesses!~
@4948 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-A vampire?! Ugh! Cold lips, no sense of rhyme!~
@4949 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Imagine the bite marks!~
@4950 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-And their mirrors never work!~
@4951 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Truly, the saddest kind of immortality. Oh, and before you get too excited: that was, of course, the wrong answer to our riddle.~
@4952 = ~How very pedestrian.~
@4953 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-All right! One last riddle, the ultimate test of mortal wit!~
@4954 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Oh, wonderful! Go on then, Tippledew — dazzle <PRO_HIMHER> with your brilliance!~
@4955 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Me? I thought *you* had one ready!~
@4956 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Me? No. You need to think of something!~
@4957 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-I am! I’m thinking very loudly!~
@4958 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-You don’t need to think loudly — you need to think faster!~
@4959 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-...~
@4960 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Ugh, fine. We give up.~
@4961 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Yes! The clever <PRO_RACE> wins!~
@4962 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Let’s sprinkle <PRO_HIMHER> with sparks. Or maybe fairy dust.~
@4963 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Pixie dust, yes! <CHARNAME> deserves a reward for such cleverness!~
@4964 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Exactly! Here, take some of our pixie dust — just don’t rub it in your eyes, all right?~
@4965 = ~^0xE3B0FFTippledew: ^-Near your face? But your face is so *unsparkly*!~
@4966 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-It needs help! Urgent sparkle intervention!~
@4967 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Come, Tippledew — initiate sparkle retreat protocol!~
@4968 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Careful, wanderer… if we stop sparkling near your face, who will keep your bad dreams away?~
@4969 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3Tippledew: ^-A wish?! Did you hear that, Lilafern? A *wish*!~
@4970 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Quick, where did we put the paperwork? The forms? The regulations on improbable miracles?!~
@4971 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3Tippledew: ^-Shh! We’re off duty tonight. Last wish we granted turned a toad into... a slimy smaller toad.~
@4972 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Very confusing for everyone involved.~
@4973 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3Tippledew: ^-But! If you wish for laughter or moonlight, we can manage those. They’re in surplus.~
@4974 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Anything bigger, and you’ll have to speak with our superior. That’s Eldath, obviously. She’s terrible with scheduling, though.~
@4975 = ~^0xFFE3B0FF Lilafern: ^-Fine, pass. Tread softly, tall one — the grass remembers footsteps.~
@4976 = ~^0xFF9ADCE3 Tippledew: ^-Come back when you’re not in such a hurry. We like conversations that wander in circles.~
@4977 = ~You darrre to attack me? Me?~
@4978 = ~Foolish morrrtal! Another soul forrr my collection!~
@4979 = ~You purrrchased the wish scroll! My congrrratulations on such a rrrrare acquisition. Before you go, a small detail — and a currrrious one at that.~
@4980 = ~The scrrroll’s ink is... volatile, shall we say. It holds its powerrr only forrr a shorrrt while afterrr purrrchase. Forrrgive me, I may have forrrgotten to mention that. Call me grrreedy, but I am a merrrchant after all, yes? Best to use it while the magic is still awake. What is the point of a wish unspoken?~
@4981 = ~Go on, trrry it right here, at once! Simple worrrds, clear intent — that’s all it takes. And should you find yourrrself strrruck speechless by joy... do rrremember who made it possible: me!~
@4982 = ~You deceived me. You should have told me that before!~
@4983 = ~If you say so...~
@4984 = ~Oh, no deceit, my frrriend! The scrrroll worrrks exactly as you imagine it does. I merrrely... omitted a minorrr detail. Forgive a merrrchant his little secrrrets.~
@4985 = ~But of courrrse! Why would a successful merrrchant such as myself everrr deceive you?~
@4986 = ~A trrravelerrr of taste and coin apprrroaches! A thousand welcomes to you. I trrrade in currriosities and comforrrts, trrrinkets and temptations — all perrrfectly harrrmless, of courrrse.~
@4987 = ~Show me what you have for sale.~
@4988 = ~You have a strange accent.~
@4989 = ~You keep some rather unusual things in your shop.~
@4990 = ~What do you sell?~
@4991 = ~No thanks, I’m just passing through.~
@4992 = ~So then, will you be buying something afterrr all?~
@4993 = ~Unusual? I prrreferrr selective. Everrry item here has a storrry — and some storrries simply... rrrefuse to end.~
@4994 = ~Strrrangeness sells, my frrriend. Orrrdinarrry things have such dull appetites. Still, I admirrre yourrr eye — most pass by without noticing that my currriosities notice them back.~
@4995 = ~With delight! Step closerrr, do not be shy. In the marrrketplace of destiny, hesitation is the costliest of habits.~
@4996 = ~As you wish, wandererrr. The rrroad forrrgets no footstep — and my warrres, no gaze.~
@4997 = ~A question most welcome! I trrrade in the currrrious and the uncommon — things you neverrr knew you needed until you see them.~
@4998 = ~But among such trrrifles, there is one trrreasurrre of trrrue legend — a scrrroll of *Wish*!~
@4999 = ~Yesss, you hearrrd it rrright: *Wish*! The spell that bends the earrr of fate itself. I came by it thrrrough a barrrgain with a Djinn of the Calim Desert.~
@5000 = ~He told me it would answerrr any voice that darrred to command it. No tedious study, no cirrrcles of rrrunes — only the courrrage to speak one’s hearrrt aloud. Of courrrse, the scroll carrres a prrrice — I must have my sharrre as well! But surrrely a herrro such as yourrrself deserrrves to tempt destiny once, no?~
@5001 = ~A scroll of Wish, you say? Sounds too good to be true.~
@5002 = ~Let me see that scroll.~
@5003 = ~No thanks. I’ll stick to bottled laughter.~
@5004 = ~Too good to be trrrue? But trrruth has never been the measurrre of value, has it? What matterrrs is that it worrrks.~
@5005 = ~You doubt, yet you’rrre still listening. That’s the marrrk of a wise buyerrr. Tell you what — take a look at the scrrript yourself. The worrrds are simple, almost childlike. Even fate enjoys a good jest now and then.~
@5006 = ~Rrreally? You noticed? A trrrade tongue frrrom the South — a blend of Calimshan courrrt and deserrrt wind. Some call it exotic... otherrrs, disconcerrrting. But accents, like faces, are only masks, my frrriend.~
@5007 = ~Now, shall we talk of warrres, not worrrds?~
@5008 = ~That accent... I’ve heard it mentioned before. A merchant with your voice took two faeries from the forest.~
@5009 = ~Fine, let’s see your wares then.~
@5010 = ~Fairrries? How quaint. You trrravel farrr, and yourrr tales trrravel even farrrtherrr. Surrrely, you don’t mean to accuse *me* of... collecting insects in jarrrs?~
@5011 = ~But if you find any such trrreaturrres, brrring them to me! I pay well for rrrarrrities.~
@5012 = ~It was you! Hand over the faeries — now!~
@5013 = ~Very well, if you say so. I’ll be on my way, then.~
@5014 = ~So the act is overrr, then. Such a pity — I was enjoying the charrrade. You morrrtals always prrreach of justice and compassion... yet yourrr eyes gleam with the same grrreedy light as mine.~
@5015 = ~Verrrry well. Come, then — claim your rrreward in claws and flame!~
